[Pre-reflection] Potential weaknesses include potential for high drawdowns due to large stop losses, reliance on multiple indicators that may not always align perfectly, and lack of consideration for other market conditions.  If results are poor (negative return), I would try adjusting parameters such as bollinger bands upper and middle, or even removing some indicators in favor of less complex setups. For mediocre results (low Sharpe), increasing the number of trades might be a possibility. An alternative approach could be to use machine learning techniques for better prediction and optimization of the strategy.
